The colonies ramify producing a bouquet-like structure (Fig. 26A) or mostly grow in one plane (Fig. 26
B-C
), in some cases, the holdfast extends for some distance along the substrate producing many more branches in a fringing-like colony that in some cases is growing upside down. The polyps are orange to yellow (Fig. 26
A-B
). In the examined specimens the larger sclerites reach up to 0.2 mm long. The branches vary in diameter from 6-10 mm, in some cases few bifurcations occur forming candelabrum-like colonies or single finger-like short branches joint by extending holdfast.
